item.title: Java Notes
item.description: Java Java is an Object-Oriented language, can be coffee too, but in this case, we’re making notes on the programming language. Java is a high-level programming language originally developed by Sun Microsystems and released in 1995. Java runs on a variety of platforms, such as Windows, Mac OS, and the various versions of UNIX. These are my simple notes for reference online. Collection of objects that communicate via invoking each other’s methods
